# --- Generic Node.js / React Project Ignores ---
# These patterns will apply within any subdirectory

# --- Dependencies ---
# Ignore node_modules directory found anywhere within subdirectories
**/node_modules/

# --- Build Output ---

# And still keep the general pattern
**/dist/
**/build/
**/out/
**/.next/
**/.vercel/
**/*.js.map
**/*.css.map

# Ignore Yarn Plug'n'Play files (optional)
**/.pnp.*
**/.yarn/*
!**/.yarn/patches
!**/.yarn/plugins
!**/.yarn/releases
!**/.yarn/sdks
!**/.yarn/versions

# --- Logs ---
# Ignore log files found anywhere within subdirectories
**/logs/
**/*.log
**/npm-debug.log*
**/yarn-debug.log*
**/yarn-error.log*
**/pnpm-debug.log*

# --- Environment Variables ---
# Ignore environment variable files found anywhere - DO NOT COMMIT THESE!
**/.env
**/.env.local
**/.env.development.local
**/.env.test.local
**/.env.production.local
**/.env.*.local

# Keep template/example env files (if you have them)
# !**/.env.example
# !**/.env.template

# --- Testing & Coverage ---
# Ignore test reports and coverage output found anywhere within subdirectories
**/coverage/
**/junit.xml
**/*.lcov

# --- IDE / Editor Specific ---
# Ignore common IDE/editor config directories found anywhere within subdirectories
**/.idea/
**/.vscode/
# To share specific VS Code settings within any project, un-ignore them:
# !**/.vscode/settings.json
# !**/.vscode/tasks.json
# !**/.vscode/launch.json
# !**/.vscode/extensions.json
**/*.sublime-project
**/*.sublime-workspace

# --- Temporary Files & Cache ---
**/.cache/
**/*.tmp
**/*.temp

# --- Miscellaneous ---
**/*.graphql.schema.json
**/schema.graphql

# === Global Ignores (Apply everywhere, including the root) ===
# These usually don't need the '**/' prefix

# --- Operating System Files ---
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
Desktop.ini
*~
*.swp
*.swo

**/.DS_Store
**/artifacts
**/cache